        <abstract>
            <p>Returns book with thanks. "Joyfully accepts" idea of the warming of Southern Hemisphere during glacial period in the Northern. Lyell is unwilling.</p> 
<p>Mentions H. N. Moseley’s study of descent of glaciers [<hi rend="italic">Proc. R. Soc. Lond.</hi> 17 (1869): 202–8].</p> 
            <p>CD greatly troubled by problem of age of the earth and calculations of Sir William Thomson. Asks about changes in the form of the globe.</p>
        </abstract>
